Method Detail

getAdrOfID

public static int getAdrOfID(java.lang.String id)
This method extracts the address (index of first byte) from am access constant.

Parameters:
id - access constant
Returns:
address

Description:
This helper method is usefull to get parameters with a length of more than 16 or 32 byte from a data container, which cannot be read by use of an access constant

Example:
getAdrOfID(FEDM_ISC_TMP_DESTROY_EPC) returns 832

getMemIDOfID

Parameters:
id - access constant
Returns:
memory ID

Example:
getAdrOfID(FEDM_ISC_TMP_DESTROY_EPC) returns 10 for TMPDATA_MEM

toRAM

public static java.lang.String toRAM(java.lang.String id)
This method modifies the memory ID of an access constant.

Parameters:
id - access constant
Returns:
id modified access constant

Description:
This helper method is usefull to get/set configuration parameters in the data container
RAMDATA_MEM by use of the access constants for EEDATA_MEM

Example:
reader.setData(toRAM(FEDM_ISC_EE_IO_ACTIVE_S_LED_G), (byte)1);
